00:00:21.480 --> 00:00:38.480
&gt;&gt; Dulce: I 

00:00:38.480 --> 00:00:44.090
went Greek because I wanted to get involved
on campus, and um, just with a closer group

00:00:44.090 --> 00:00:47.640
and make the UT Community smaller.\
&gt;&gt; Emily: When I came into UT I realized,

00:00:47.640 --> 00:00:52.800
wow this school is really big. And I needed
to make some friends and feel a sense of community

00:00:52.800 --> 00:00:56.110
to make it feel like a home not just a big
school.\

00:00:56.110 --> 00:01:01.110
&gt;&gt; Kanishka: I went Greek because when I came
to UT it was just so overwhelming. Like, it's

00:01:01.110 --> 00:01:04.790
such a big campus and community and I was
trying to find my own inner circle.\

00:01:04.790 --> 00:01:09.080
&gt;&gt; Milam: That sense of brotherhood or sisterhood
from joining a fraternity is unmatchable.

00:01:09.080 --> 00:01:14.381
If you need somebody to go eat lunch with
you can call up one of your friends. If you

00:01:14.381 --> 00:01:17.830
need somebody to go study with you can call
up one of your friends. There's always somebody

00:01:17.830 --> 00:01:25.330
to turn to, uh, when you have that community
from being in a fraternity or a sorority.

00:01:25.330 --> 00:01:26.330
\
