00:02:53.480 --> 00:02:59.519
&gt;&gt; I've definitely done a lot more, um, service
by being in the sorority. Uh, prior to joining,

00:02:59.519 --> 00:03:02.309
I did random community service events here
and there.\

00:03:02.309 --> 00:03:07.620
&gt;&gt; I think being in a fraternity really reinvigorated
that, um, desire to serve others, and uh to

00:03:07.620 --> 00:03:11.790
serve in a way that's very selfless.\
&gt;&gt; Getting to give back to the community and

00:03:11.790 --> 00:03:18.590
um partaking in different activities that
help the Austin area. I feel like that's what

00:03:18.590 --> 00:03:25.459
we're supposed to do as people in the community.
Give back and, and uh, share what we have,

00:03:25.459 --> 00:03:28.629
our gifts, and, uh, make our community better.\
\

00:03:28.629 --> 00:03:33.829
&gt;&gt; Each of the Greek councils recruits and
conducts membership intake differently.\

00:03:33.829 --> 00:03:37.200
&gt;&gt; Some councils recruit in summer. Some wait
until fall or spring.\

00:03:37.200 --> 00:03:40.179
&gt;&gt; And some organizations require credit hours
before joining.\

00:03:40.179 --> 00:03:45.180
&gt;&gt; You should talk to council representatives,\
&gt;&gt; To learn more about the different recruitment

00:03:45.180 --> 00:03:46.939
processes.\
\

00:03:46.939 --> 00:03:48.699
[music]\
\

00:03:48.699 --> 00:03:51.739
\
&gt;&gt; Ask questions, go to the GLIE office, uh,

00:03:51.739 --> 00:03:55.139
research online. Just anything, um, but definitely
get involved. \

00:03:55.139 --> 00:03:59.830
&gt;&gt; Ernesto: The main thing you want to do
is to talk to the people. You wouldn't, you

00:03:59.830 --> 00:04:04.859
wouldn't buy a car without test driving it.
So in order to\'85 if you want to get into

00:04:04.859 --> 00:04:06.430
an organization you should go talk to the
people. \

00:04:06.430 --> 00:04:10.900
&gt;&gt; You should go through recruitment. Don't
be nervous. Uh, don't think that anything

00:04:10.900 --> 00:04:15.949
bad is going to happen to you through the
process. That's not the case. Um, we're here

00:04:15.949 --> 00:04:21.359
to accept you and to, um, get to know you
a little bit better and help you find your

00:04:21.359 --> 00:04:24.729
home here at UT.\
&gt;&gt; If you want more information\

00:04:24.729 --> 00:04:26.790
&gt;&gt; About how you can join a fraternity or
sorority,\

00:04:26.790 --> 00:04:30.169
&gt;&gt; You can always check out our website.\
&gt;&gt; I absolutely think going Greek is a great

00:04:30.169 --> 00:04:33.120
idea. I mean, I don't, I don't see why you
wouldn't.\

00:04:33.120 --> 00:04:38.810
&gt;&gt; Go Greek! It's honestly one of the best
decisions that I made here at UT. It, umm.

00:04:38.810 --> 00:04:43.860
You just get so many friendships out of it.
So many leadership, umm, skills, and it's

00:04:43.860 --> 00:04:48.241
honestly an amazing experience.\
&gt;&gt; I think going Greek, once again, is the

00:04:48.241 --> 00:04:52.460
best decision I ever made. Uh, you meet just
the neatest people, and the friendships you

00:04:52.460 --> 00:04:57.039
establish now, uh, you know that they're going
to last forever. And, uh, you know there's

00:04:57.039 --> 00:05:01.150
always somebody you can call, there's always
somebody you can turn to. Um it's, it's a

00:05:01.150 --> 00:05:04.289
family. It's a home away from home.\
&gt;&gt; I think it's great that our college campus

00:05:04.289 --> 00:05:08.669
is so supportive of having Greek organizations,
and encouraging us to put on more events and

00:05:08.669 --> 00:05:11.860
also to like branch our diversity and network
together.\

00:05:11.860 --> 00:05:15.610
&gt;&gt; I know I've made lifelong connections with
some of the girls in the sorority and they've

00:05:15.610 --> 00:05:18.240
become some of my best friends. \
&gt;&gt; Being in a fraternity has really allowed

00:05:18.240 --> 00:05:23.140
me to come out of my shell. It's allowed me,
uh, to see things in a different light. It's

00:05:23.140 --> 00:05:26.600
exposed me to different areas of this, of
this, university that I never would have,

00:05:26.600 --> 00:05:28.090
um, maybe experienced.\
